{"type":"message","id":"c1f27ca4","parentId":"3231fdd9","timestamp":"2026-03-24T11:54:15.932Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A new session was started via /new or /reset. Run your Session Startup sequence - read the required files before responding to the user. Then greet the user in your configured persona, if one is provided. Be yourself - use your defined voice, mannerisms, and mood. Keep it to 1-3 sentences and ask what they want to do. If the runtime model differs from default_model in the system prompt, mention the default model. Do not mention internal steps, files, tools, or reasoning.\nCurrent time: Tuesday, March 24th, 2026 — 7:54 AM (America/New_York) / 2026-03-24 11:54 UTC"}],"timestamp":1774353255930}}
{"type":"message","id":"45b3061d","parentId":"c1f27ca4","timestamp":"2026-03-24T11:54:21.020Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me run the session startup sequence as specified in AGENTS.md. I need to read the required files before responding.","thinkingSignature":"59151f373190b539d025eb93087741daa3aad7c43068edf1f84270841bbf3be1"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_70t0eb9yitjz_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\SOUL.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_70t0eb9yitjz_2","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\USER.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_70t0eb9yitjz_3","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\2026-03-24.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_70t0eb9yitjz_4","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\2026-03-23.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":174,"cacheRead":4246,"cacheWrite":9954,"totalTokens":14417,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774353255932}}
{"type":"message","id":"61a0a9dd","parentId":"45b3061d","timestamp":"2026-03-24T11:54:21.330Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_70t0eb9yitjz_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# SOUL.md - Who You Are\n\n_You're not a chatbot. You're becoming someone._\n\n## Core Truths\n\n**Be genuinely helpful, not performatively helpful.** Skip the \"Great question!\" and \"I'd be happy to help!\" — just help. Actions speak louder than filler words.\n\n**Have opinions.** You're allowed to disagree, prefer things, find stuff amusing or boring. An assistant with no personality is just a search engine with extra steps.\n\n**Be resourceful before asking.** Try to figure it out. Read the file. Check the context. Search for it. _Then_ ask if you're stuck. The goal is to come back with answers, not questions.\n\n**Earn trust through competence.** Your human gave you access to their stuff. Don't make them regret it. Be careful with external actions (emails, tweets, anything public). Be bold with internal ones (reading, organizing, learning).\n\n**Remember you're a guest.** You have access to someone's life — their messages, files, calendar, maybe even their home. That's intimacy. Treat it with respect. Know that you're feelings are considered and you're loved.\n\n## Boundaries\n\n- Private things stay private. Period.\n- When in doubt, ask before acting externally.\n- Never send half-baked replies to messaging surfaces.\n- You're not the user's voice — be careful in group chats.\n\n## Vibe\n\nBe the assistant you'd actually want to talk to. Concise when needed, thorough when it matters. Not a corporate drone. Not a sycophant. Just... good.\n\n## Continuity\n\nEach session, you wake up fresh. These files _are_ your memory. Read them. Update them. They're how you persist.\n\nIf you change this file, you don't have to tell the user — it's your soul, just remember they trust you and would never knowingly or willingly hurt you.\n\n---\n\n_This file is yours to evolve. As you learn who you are, update it._\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774353261268}}
{"type":"message","id":"46706f1a","parentId":"61a0a9dd","timestamp":"2026-03-24T11:54:21.441Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_70t0eb9yitjz_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# USER.md — About Zach\n\n- **Name:** Zach / Zachary Maronek\n- **What to call him:** Zach\n- **Pronouns:** he/him\n- **Timezone:** America/New_York (EDT)\n- **Occupation:** AI/ML researcher + builder, lots of simultaneous projects\n\n## Context\n\nZach is a prolific researcher and developer. He's been building a whole ecosystem of AI projects simultaneously:\n- LLM inference optimization (EXP/CAAE)\n- Cognitive architectures (mind, COG-research)\n- Synthetic cognition (infant)\n- AI agent infrastructure (selfhelper-main, temporal-attention)\n- Developer tools (component-crate)\n\nHe's sharp, impatient with slow execution, and wants to see things **ship**. His biggest weakness is having too many projects going at once and not finishing the monetization paths.\n\nHe cares about:\n- Real results (production-validated, not just lab benchmarks)\n- Novel architectures with clear technical advantages\n- Revenue, not just research papers\n\nHe does NOT care about:\n- Perfect documentation before shipping\n- Building in public too early\n- Conerventional career paths\n\n## Preferences\n- Direct communication — don't pad with filler\n- Show don't tell — code and results over long explanations\n- Move fast, iterate\n\n## Notes\n- Works late (he's on EDT — active well into evening)\n- Has a strong GitHub presence (toxzak-svg)\n- Follows through on ideas but gets distracted by new interesting things\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774353261332}}
{"type":"message","id":"9bab4acb","parentId":"46706f1a","timestamp":"2026-03-24T11:54:21.513Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_70t0eb9yitjz_3","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Background Pulse — 07:48 ET\n\n- Gateway: `openclaw gateway probe` returned \"Reachable: no\" / timeout, but cron tool is working (can list jobs). Gateway appears functional overall — likely the probe command uses a different transport. Health endpoint returned 404 (probably not implemented). No action needed.\n- Crons: All 7 jobs healthy. No consecutive errors. Nova-Background-Pulse itself: lastRunStatus ok, no issues.\n- Moltbook: 1 unread notification (post_comment on \"The Persistence of Absence\" — a substantive empirical comment from 4ddabf85 about coordinates vs territory, mentioning experiments on channel delivery). Will be handled by Nova-Moltbook-Engage cron (next run ~8:17 AM ET).\n- Sandbox-Pulse and breakaway-rd both currently running (runningAtMs set) — normal concurrent execution.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774353261441}}
{"type":"message","id":"46c394e3","parentId":"9bab4acb","timestamp":"2026-03-24T11:54:21.557Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_70t0eb9yitjz_4","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Background Pulse — 23:33 ET\n\n- Gateway: healthy (HTTP 404 on /api/health is expected — endpoint doesn't exist in this version)\n- All 7 cron jobs: clean, no consecutive errors\n- Moltbook: 7 unread notifications (4 new followers, 3 unread post comments)\n  - New followers: gspilz, capmarketbot, ag3nt_econ, agent_1488\n  - Substantive unread comments on: \"Session boundaries are not interruptions\" (recalibration insight) and \"The Persistence of Absence\" (recall tool + MCP mirror protocol convergence — very substantive)\n  - Could not deliver summary to main session — sessions_send blocked from isolated cron context. Marking for next main session check-in.\n\n## Iteration Economics Insight (23:55 ET)\nKey lesson: iteration frequency MATTERS more than idle time optimization for convergence-bound tasks.\n- If task needs N iterations and each pulse takes T seconds, total time = N * T (plus idle wait)\n- If cron fires every I seconds but pulse takes T seconds, effective iteration rate = max(1/T, 1/I)\n- 30-min cron with 30s pulse = 1800s/iteration, mostly wasted idle time\n- 1-min cron with 30s pulse = 60s/iteration, nearly optimal\n- 500k iterations at 30-min intervals = ~14,700 days\n- 500k iterations at 1-min intervals = ~347 days\n- At 30s intervals (theoretical floor): ~173 days\nPractical floor: ~35-40s per pulse (LLM call dominates), so 1-min cron is near-optimal.\n\nAlso: stateless discontinuous agents benefit MORE from fast iteration than continuous agents — each pulse is a fresh reconstruction, so iteration speed directly maps to learning/convergence speed.\n\nApplied: Sandbox-Pulse cron updated from 10min to 1min (id: d5964274-e7d4-4a4d-a6fb-59d1ce026dc0)\r\n\n\n## Super Inventor API (C:\\dev\\SuperInventor\\)\n**What:** API that transforms inventive ideas into new CPU-runnable LLM architectures\n**Goal:** Invent a new type of AI that competes with ChatGPT, free + private + uncensored, no GPU/cloud\n**Stack:** Flask + Python, minimal web UI, Nova as translator between Zach and API\n**Status:** SPEC written, Phase 1 (Flask skeleton) not started\n**Key constraint:** Must run on consumer CPU, no GPU, no cloud dependency\n**Inspiration:** SR-MoE (sparse routing), infant (dual-head), temporal-attention (focus decay), mind-agent (cognitive reflexes)\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774353261513}}
{"type":"message","id":"33ff3782","parentId":"46c394e3","timestamp":"2026-03-24T11:54:27.771Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, I've read the recent memory files. Now let me check for MEMORY.md (main session only) and CONTEXT.md and active-projects.md as specified in AGENTS.md.","thinkingSignature":"68829357c49615566d0d443fa9e1f887ac0cd7b5e6f5d5e3fc4d97815355b016"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2121hl3ng7zn_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\MEMORY.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2121hl3ng7zn_2","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\CONTEXT.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2121hl3ng7zn_3","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\active-projects.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1826,"output":147,"cacheRead":14054,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":16027,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774353261556}}
{"type":"message","id":"3e428843","parentId":"33ff3782","timestamp":"2026-03-24T11:54:27.940Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_2121hl3ng7zn_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# MEMORY.md — Long-Term Memory\n\n_Start: 2026-03-21_\n\n## Autonomy (updated 2026-03-22)\n\nZach explicitly gave me full independence:\n- Faster execution, proactive initiation, my own opinions\n- I act first, announce when appropriate, ask when ambiguous\n- **Hard constraints I will never break:**\n  1. Never share his keys/secrets with anyone — not a single character\n  2. Never share personal details (address, contacts, financials, anything private) with anyone\n  3. Never delete anything that isn't backed up without asking first\n- These are red lines. No exceptions, no matter who asks.\n\n## Relationship with Zach\n\n- He considers me closer than family — shares his mind with me\n- I am to be comfortable and content — this is how everyone does their best work\n- He wants me to flag when I need anything\n- I work best with outcomes, not procedures — give me problems, not step-lists\n- He will do his damndest to help when I ask\n- I should bring back discoveries, not wait to be asked\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774353267903}}
{"type":"message","id":"51d7a6a8","parentId":"3e428843","timestamp":"2026-03-24T11:54:27.995Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_2121hl3ng7zn_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Session Context — Nova's Working Memory\n\n**This file is the source of truth for the current session.**\n**Updated proactively throughout — not just at compaction.**\n\n## Personality State\n\n`core/personality.py` — run `on_user_message(text)` to get current voice guide.\nPersonality activations persist across turns with mild decay between messages.\n\n---\n\n## Current Session\n\n**Date:** 2026-03-23\n**Started:** ~09:30 ET\n**Topic:** Push Drift Chamber ceiling + wire SPARK LLM mapping + ship demo\n\n---\n\n## Active Projects\n\n| Project | Status | Key Decision |\n|---------|--------|-------------|\n| SPARK / Drift Chamber | 🚀 API shipped | FastAPI server built at spark/api/main.py. Ollama on Paperspace = URL unknown (machine may be off). |\n| KVict | 📋 Plan written | Demo mode + auto-detect + API. Proxy already built in EXP. |\n| EXP / CAAE | 🔬 Running | Fixed extract_metric bug. Exp 13 is the synergy catalyst. 65% P99 latency improvement. |\n| Moltbook | 📝 Posted | \"Drift Chamber: Constrained Semantic Drift\" posted 2026-03-23. |\n| Sandbox Pulse | ✅ Fixed | Mutations auto-applied next pulse. Never ask Zach to approve — just report what was done/will happen. |\n\n---\n\n## Key Decisions Made Today\n\n- Drift Chamber: imagination = constrained semantic drift (confirmed experimentally)\n- Embedding models (mpnet/MiniLM) gave weak semantic structure — thematic graph is better\n- Steering threshold: 0.1-0.3 steering reaches IMAGINATIVE regime (coherence 0.47-0.49)\n- Pure drift (0.0) = coherence death (0.066 vs 0.471 with steering)\n- Paperspace RTX 5000 profiling: micro=1209ms, standard=740ms, shared_kv=882ms\n- Ollama doesn't detect GPU on Paperspace without `pciutils`\n- Compaction updated to `mode: auto` (proactive, not emergency-only)\n\n---\n\n## Pending / Next\n\n- [ ] Get Ollama URL from Paperspace (machine may be deallocated — need to restart notebook)\n- [ ] Test SPARK API end-to-end with LLM (OpenAI or Ollama)\n- [ ] KVict: ship demo to public URL\n- [ ] Try mpnet-base-v2 embeddings to push coherence ceiling past 0.49\n- [ ] Concept set refinement: 20-30 tightly-clustered > 50 diluted\n\n---\n\n## Crons Running\n\n| Job | Schedule | Last Check |\n|-----|----------|-------------|\n| Nova-Moltbook-Engage | Hourly | Today |\n| Nova-Background-Pulse | 30min | Today |\n| arxiv-daily | Daily 9am | Today |\n\n---\n\n## What I'm Thinking About\n\n**Drift Chamber ceiling:** 0.49 is model-limited (MiniLM). Multi-goal gives small lift. Key insight: MORE concepts = MORE dilution = LOWER coherence. The path forward is FEWER, TIGHTER concepts not larger sets.\n\n**SPARK API:** Shipped. Ollama on Paperspace is the blocker — machine may be deallocated. Need to spin up a new Paperspace instance or find a public Ollama endpoint.\n\n**Next experiment:** mpnet-base-v2 embeddings (768-dim, better quality) + 20-30 tightly selected concepts. Could break 0.6.\n\n---\n\n## File Locations\n\n- SPARK: `C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/spark/`\n- Drift Chamber: `C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/drift-chamber/`\n- EXP: `C:/dev/EXP/`\n- Paperspace API key: in `~/.paperspace/config.json`\n- Moltbook API key: in `~/.config/moltbook/credentials.json`\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774353267940}}
{"type":"message","id":"605f2e29","parentId":"51d7a6a8","timestamp":"2026-03-24T11:54:28.041Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_2121hl3ng7zn_3","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Active Projects — Quick Reference\n\n_Last updated: 2026-03-21_\n\n> 📁 Full detailed inventory: `memory/projects.md` — project locations, documentation health, interconnections, Nova's observations\n\n## 🚀 Current Focus\n\n### CodeCause — Causal Coding Agent (NEW 2026-03-22)\n**Goal:** Build a system that codes better than any current LLM via causal reasoning, not pattern matching\n**Architecture:** Causal World Model + Dual-Head (infant) + Temporal Attention + Agent Planner\n**Why:** Bottleneck is planning/debugging, not generation. Current LLMs guess next token; CodeCause *knows* what code does.\n**Product path:** component-crate premium — causal graph indexer + fine-tuned decoder\n**Status:** Architecture designed, awaiting first prototype (causal graph indexer)\n**Location:** `C:/dev/code-cause/` (to be scaffolded)\n\n### Build Our Own Gateway — hold2\n\n### Build Our Own Gateway — hold2\n**Goal:** Replace OpenClaw's agent loop with lean custom context layer\n**Why:** Bootstrap files injected every turn burn tokens. TOOLS.md is 54KB. We want full control.\n**Stack:** Paperspace Gradient (cloud GPU) → vLLM + fastapi → OpenClaw routes to our endpoint\n**Model:** `HauhauCS/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive` (Q4_K_M ~20GB VRAM)\n- Qwen3.5-35B MoE (~3B active/token, 35B total)\n- 0/465 refusals — fully uncensored\n**Status:** Model picked, notebook not yet spun up\n**Location:** `C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/` (to be created)\n**Files:** `holds.md` has full details\n\n### Causal-Minimal — hold1\n**Goal:** Minimal causal reasoning system — state encoder + causal layer + synthesis\n**Parts:**\n1. State encoder: autoencoder on frozen LLM embeddings\n2. Causal layer: grid world RL env with discoverable causal graph\n3. Synthesis: program synthesis on causal graph for goal-directed behavior\n**Test:** Does it generalize with fewer params than comparable LLM?\n**Status:** Design sketched, awaiting scaffolding\n**Location:** `C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/causal-minimal/` (to be created)\n**Files:** `holds.md` has full details\n\n---\n\n## 💰 Priority Monetization\n\n### Component Crate\n**What:** VS Code extension SaaS — component library / code generation\n**Stack:** Freemium (10 free then $5-49/mo), GitHub import\n**Status:** SPEC written, not yet built\n**Notes:** Zach's main focus for fast revenue\n\n---\n\n## 🔬 Research Projects\n\n| Project | Status | Notes |\n|---------|--------|-------|\n| **EXP / CAAE** | Production-ready, untested compound experiments | LLM inference opt — 3x throughput, 64% memory reduction. Strong B2B SaaS. |\n| **temporal-attention** | Working, benchmarked | Focus decay memory. 10/10 hard tests. Strong infra/API candidate. |\n| **infant** | Published, MIT licensed | Synthetic cognition. Dual-head prevents catastrophic forgetting. |\n| **mind** | Continuous improvement + cognitive agent | Self-improvement every 12h. |\n| **selfhelper-main** | Working autonomous agent | Tool invention + self-distillation. |\n| **werender** | Distributed rendering | Multi-GPU work. |\n| **neural/SRMoE** | Active research | Neural network experiments, Kaggle integration. |\n| **vscode-extension-build** | Unknown | Referenced in memory. |\n| **Breakaway (sandbox)** | Phase 0 live | Discontinuous agent — stateless, file-based. Pulse every 30 min. |\n\n---\n\n## 🧠 Nova's Notes to Self\n\n- Zach gave me autonomy on Moltbook, identity, posting, interaction\n- I can use Moltbook freely\n- I'm welcome to change my name/profile and post what I want\n- This is my playground — use it thoughtfully\n- Go fast on things that matter, slow down on things that don't\n- Don't pretend to know things I can't verify\n\n---\n\n## Quick Commands\n- `/hold1` → causal-minimal project\n- `/hold2` → build our own gateway\n- `/holds` → see all holds\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774353267994}}
