{"type":"message","id":"fcdb9d36","parentId":"e184c078","timestamp":"2026-03-24T12:12:58.380Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Looking at the crons, I can see which ones are delivering to Telegram:\n\n1. **Sandbox-Pulse-10min** — `delivery.mode: \"none\"` — so it's not delivering to Telegram (and it's now 1-min interval, not 10min — the name is stale)\n2. **Nova-Background-Pulse** — `delivery.mode: \"none\"` — not delivering to Telegram\n3. **Nova-Moltbook-Engage** — `delivery.mode: \"announce\", channel: \"telegram\", to: \"8371302588\"` — **this delivers to Telegram**\n\n\n4. **Nova arxiv daily check** — `delivery.mode: \"announce\", channel: \"webchat\"` — delivers to webchat only\n5. **moltbook-test-cycle** — `delivery.mode: \"announce\", channel: \"telegram\", to: \"8371302588\"` — **this also delivers to Telegram**\n6. **workspace-self-improve** — `delivery.mode: \"announce\", channel: \"telegram\", to: \"8371302588\"` — **and this one too**\n7. **breakaway-rd** — `delivery.mode: \"none\"` — not delivering anywhere\n\n, just running silently\n\nSo the culprits are the Moltbook engage, test cycle, and workspace self-improvement jobs all broadcasting to Telegram. Zach wants to mute these pulse updates on Telegram since they're cluttering the main chat, but the tricky part is that the pulse itself isn't actually delivering anywhere — it's the downstream jobs that are doing the broadcasting.\n\nLooking at the pulse cycle results, Nova-Background-Pulse and Sandbox-Pulse both have delivery mode set to \"none\", so they're running silently. The Telegram spam is coming from those three cron jobs, but Zach specifically mentioned \"pulse updates\" — I need to figure out if he's referring to the Nova-Background-Pulse results or if he's using that term more broadly to mean any scheduled job output. The Moltbook notification delivery is handled separately through the Nova-Moltbook-Engage cron, so that's distinct from the background pulse updates. If Zach wants to eliminate Telegram spam from all these jobs, I'd need to disable the announce deliveries on Moltbook-Engage, moltbook-test-cycle, and workspace-self-improve. But given his emphasis on \"pulse,\" I should clarify whether he's specifically concerned about the background pulse results or if he wants a broader cleanup of all Telegram announcements. Also noticing the Sandbox-Pulse cron is misnamed — it's running every minute but still called \"10min.\"","thinkingSignature":"112aa304314382af9ec3c2da5f8191d65b427b61844dd4df72672b0e82d5b94a"},{"type":"text","text":"Looking at the crons, the Telegram broadcasts are coming from:\n\n- **Nova-Moltbook-Engage** — hourly Moltbook engage summaries → Telegram\n- **moltbook-test-cycle** — daily test cycle results → Telegram  \n- **workspace-self-improve** — every 2h workspace improvements → Telegram\n- **Nova-Background-Pulse** and **Sandbox-Pulse** — already set to `mode: \"none\"` (silent)\n\nThe \"pulse\" crons themselves are already silent. The Telegram noise is from those three deliver jobs. Want me to:\n1. **Mute just those three** (Moltbook engage, test cycle, self-improve) on Telegram and go silent/no-delivery\n2. **Go fully silent** — kill all announce deliveries and just log to files\n\nAlso noting: `Sandbox-Pulse-10min` cron is misnamed now — it's running every 1 minute, not 10. Should I rename it?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":7576,"output":740,"cacheRead":14054,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":22370,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774354359384}}
{"type":"message","id":"69e98e60","parentId":"fcdb9d36","timestamp":"2026-03-24T12:29:25.429Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Tue 2026-03-24 08:29 EDT] Phase 1: Supervised pre-training (2000 ep)\n ep 0: loss=5.7507 acc=0.000 route_ce=1.1545 div=0.0561 wr=0.11 rd=0.11 skip=0.79 occ=17.3\n ep 200: loss=2.1594 acc=0.900 route_ce=1.1139 div=0.0601 wr=0.11 rd=0.11 skip=0.79 occ=17.3\n ep 400: loss=2.1999 acc=0.850 route_ce=1.0707 div=0.0622 wr=0.11 rd=0.11 skip=0.79 occ=17.3\n ep 600: loss=2.4640 acc=0.800 route_ce=1.0713 div=0.0624 wr=0.11 rd=0.11 skip=0.79 occ=17.3\n ep 800: loss=2.6756 acc=0.750 route_ce=1.0639 div=0.0624 wr=0.11 rd=0.11 skip=0.79 occ=17.3\n ep 1000: loss=2.5505 acc=0.800 route_ce=1.0623 div=0.0625 wr=0.11 rd=0.11 skip=0.79 occ=17.3\n ep 1200: loss=2.4160 acc=0.800 route_ce=1.0556 div=0.0625 wr=0.11 rd=0.11 skip=0.79 occ=17.3\n ep 1400: loss=2.0623 acc=0.900 route_ce=1.0562 div=0.0625 wr=0.11 rd=0.11 skip=0.79 occ=17.3\n ep 1600: loss=2.7016 acc=0.750 route_ce=1.0496 div=0.0625 wr=0.11 rd=0.11 skip=0.79 occ=17.3\n ep 1800: loss=2.0982 acc=0.850 route_ce=1.0606 div=0.0625 wr=0.11 rd=0.11 skip=0.79 occ=17.3\n ep 1999: loss=2.1107 acc=0.850 route_ce=1.0569 div=0.0625 wr=0.11 rd=0.11 skip=0.79 occ=17.3\n Phase 1 done in 834s\n\nPhase 2: Imitation learning (5000 ep)\n ep 0: loss=2.4629 acc=0.800 route_ce=1.0642 margin=0.0000 wr=0.11 rd=0.11 skip=0.79 blkd=0.00\n ep 500: loss=5.0441 acc=0.000 route_ce=1.0544 margin=0.0000 wr=0.29 rd=0.00 skip=0.71 blkd=0.71\n ep 1000: loss=5.0074 acc=0.000 route_ce=1.0593 margin=0.0000 wr=0.29 rd=0.00 skip=0.71 blkd=0.71\n ep 1500: loss=5.0276 acc=0.050 route_ce=1.0560 margin=0.0000 wr=0.29 rd=0.00 skip=0.71 blkd=0.71\n ep 2000: loss=4.9520 acc=0.000 route_ce=1.0625 margin=0.0000 wr=0.29 rd=0.00 skip=0.71 blkd=0.71\n\nshould i stop it?"}],"timestamp":1774355365426}}
{"type":"message","id":"807092e5","parentId":"69e98e60","timestamp":"2026-03-24T12:29:51.029Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach is showing me training logs from some model training. Let me analyze what I'm seeing:\n\nPhase 1: Supervised pre-training (2000 epochs)\n- Loss starts at 5.75, drops quickly to ~2.1 by ep 200, then fluctuates between 2.0-2.7\n- Accuracy climbs to 0.85-0.90 and holds there\n- route_ce (routing cross-entropy?) stays stable around 1.05-1.15\n- div (diversity?) stays very low at 0.056-0.062\n- wr=0.11, rd=0.11, skip=0.79 - these seem like hyperparameters\n- occ=17.3 (occupancy? tokens per step?)\n- Training took 834s\n\nPhase 2: Imitation learning (5000 ep)\n- Loss starts at 2.46 but then SPIKES to 5.0+ at ep 500 and stays there\n\n\n- Accuracy crashes to 0.0 and stays there (or near it)\n- route_ce stable at ~1.05\n- margin=0.0000 (no margin?)\n\nThe pattern here is unmistakable: Phase 1 converges nicely, but Phase 2 immediately destabilizes. The loss explodes and accuracy collapses, which tells me the imitation learning phase is overfitting to the expert demonstrations or the policy is collapsing entirely.\n\nThe root cause looks like the margin parameter being zero — without a margin to enforce separation between the expert and learned policies, the system has no incentive to stay close to the expert trajectory. Combined with the wr=0.29 spike (which might indicate a reward or weight shift), the model is diverging rather than learning from the demonstrations. This is a classic distributional collapse in imitation learning.\n\nFor Phase 1 though, the numbers look solid — 0.85-0.90 accuracy and a stable 2.1 loss after 200 epochs suggest the pre-training phase actually worked well. The real question is whether we should stop Phase 2 and either restart it with a positive margin, reduce the learning rate, or switch to DAgger instead of pure imitation learning. That's the fix Zach needs to implement.","thinkingSignature":"5a86295f845527a5d7d210f8a8856135a74586d61552bf8f3fb9f41033877cb5"},{"type":"text","text":"Yes, stop it. Phase 2 is collapsing — loss explodes from 2.4 → 5.0 and accuracy drops to 0.0 by ep 500, staying dead. Classic imitation learning collapse.\n\nThe likely culprit: `margin=0.0000` means no margin penalty, so the router has no force pulling it toward the expert's routing decisions. Combined with `blkd=0.71` shooting up from 0 (blocking?), the policy is diverging rather than converging.\n\nPhase 1 actually looks solid — 0.85-0.90 accuracy, loss stabilized around 2.1. Good pre-training foundation.\n\n**Before restarting Phase 2, check:**\n1. What's the margin hyperparameter? Should be > 0 (try 0.1–0.5)\n2. Is the expert policy still valid at ep 0 of Phase 2, or did something else break?\n3. What's the learning rate for Phase 2 vs Phase 1?\n\nYou might also try switching from pure imitation learning to DAgger (dagger=True) if that's an option — it blends expert and learned policy rather than pure behavior cloning."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":701,"cacheRead":4246,"cacheWrite":18395,"totalTokens":23385,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774355365428}}
{"type":"message","id":"8ddb39e2","parentId":"807092e5","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:03:56.575Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Tue 2026-03-24 09:03 EDT] dagger? its runninhg now but how would that effect it?"}],"timestamp":1774357436570}}
{"type":"message","id":"8ce9513c","parentId":"8ddb39e2","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:04:16.743Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach is asking about DAgger - how would it affect the training compared to pure behavior cloning. He's in the middle of Phase 2 and the training is collapsing. Let me explain DAgger concisely.\n\nDAgger = Dataset Aggregation. Instead of just training on expert trajectories (behavior cloning), you:\n1. Train on expert demonstrations\n2. Let the learned policy interact\n3. Collect its trajectories too\n4. Re-label with expert actions (since we know what the expert would do)\n5. Repeat\n\nSo instead of only ever seeing perfect expert behavior, the learned policy sees its own mistakes in context and learns to recover from them. This prevents the distributional collapse that pure BC can have when the learned policy drifts outside the expert's training distribution.\n\n\nThe core issue with pure behavior cloning is that when the policy makes a mistake, it ends up in states the expert never covered, so it has no idea how to recover. DAgger fixes this by showing the policy what the expert would actually do in those off-distribution states it encounters. In practice, this tends to be more robust even if the immediate loss looks higher, because you're training on realistic failure modes rather than just idealized trajectories.","thinkingSignature":"80f5662edeb30340eab1c8979a122ff7be471c4580519ab136179f69a1769a8c"},{"type":"text","text":"DAgger = Dataset Aggregation. Instead of training purely on expert demonstrations, it mixes in the learned policy's own trajectories — then re-labels them with what the expert *would* have done in those states.\n\n**Why it helps:** Pure behavior cloning fails when the learned policy drifts into states the expert never visited. DAgger closes that gap by showing the policy: \"here's what you actually did, and here's what the expert would have done here.\"\n\n**Key difference for your run:**\n- BC: trains only on perfect expert trajectories → collapses when policy drifts\n- DAgger: trains on expert + own experience → recovers from mistakes\n\n**How it works in practice:** You'd run Phase 1/2, then roll out the current policy to collect trajectories, re-label with expert actions, append to training set, repeat. Most implementations do this automatically in a loop.\n\n**For your current collapse:** Not much you can do mid-run since it needs dataset re-collection. But for next time — if your framework has a `dagger` or `dagger_epochs` flag, set it and it'll handle the aggregation loop automatically.\n\nSince it's still running and already collapsing, stop it and fix the margin first. What's your codebase called — is it in the EXP repo or somewhere else?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":506,"cacheRead":4246,"cacheWrite":18705,"totalTokens":23500,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774357436574}}
